// ==========================================
// Autonomous Features Enabled:
// ==========================================
// ✅ Auto-restart on crash (autorestart: true)
// ✅ Memory limit protection (max_memory_restart)
// ✅ Crash loop prevention (max_restarts, min_uptime)
// ✅ Automatic logging (all output saved)
// ✅ Environment management (dev/production)
// ✅ Resource monitoring (max_memory_restart)
//
// Setup for Full Autonomy:
// 1. Start processes: pm2 start ecosystem.config.js
// 2. Save configuration: pm2 save
// 3. Enable auto-start: pm2 startup (follow instructions)
// 4. Processes run automatically on system boot
//
// Monitoring:
// - pm2 list              # See all processes
// - pm2 logs              # View logs in real-time
// - pm2 monit             # Resource usage dashboard
// - pm2 status            # Quick status check
//
// The user never needs to manually:
// - Restart crashed processes (auto-restart)
// - Start services on boot (startup script)
// - Monitor for memory leaks (auto-restart on limit)
// - Check logs manually (centralized logging)
